http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Achuthanandan-condoles-Bardhan%E2%80%99s-death/article13980199.ece

The death of A.B. Bardhan is an irreparable loss to the Leftist and secular forces in the country, Leader of the Opposition V.S. Achuthanandan has said.In a condolence message here on Sunday, Mr. Achuthanandan pointed out that Bardhan was an ideal example of a communist struggle that lasted seven and a half decades. Bardhan was a leader who set aside his life for the Communist Party and for the democratic forces. The role he played in strengthening the Left-secular forces across the country is unforgettable. He was able to give a sense of direction to the joint functioning of the two communist parties, the press note said.He had a deep understanding of Marxism-Leninism and about political movements across the world. He was able to win the affection of one and all through his simple living and affable interactions even as he was the general secretary of the CPI for 16 years, the press note added.Prominent leaderIn his condolence message, the general secretary of the Revolutionary Socialist Party (RSP) T. J. Chandrachoodan said Bardhan was prominent among those leaders who set aside their lives for the emancipation of the working class in the country.